			<description><![CDATA[<p>
We&#39;re PVPower, a solar company based in Chicago.&nbsp; We&rsquo;re a small team working hard to get more solar panels onto more roofs.&nbsp; We&rsquo;re revenue-generating, funded, and we&rsquo;re growing.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
We&rsquo;re in the process of introducing <a href="http://ownkiwi.com">Kiwi</a>, a new consumer solar brand and product to the market. It&rsquo;s the simplest, highest-value option for homeowners today and it&#39;s the future of solar.&nbsp; It&rsquo;s green, simple, made-in-the-USA, and a great investment. We need help conveying that message.</p>
<p>
PVPower is looking to build a long-term relationship with a great designer who can help us make a real difference.&nbsp;&nbsp; User experience and web design are key components of the role.&nbsp; In addition to hard skills, we&rsquo;re looking for someone who&rsquo;s enthusiastic about what we&rsquo;re doing, self-motivated, and a strong, proactive communicator.</p>
<p>
Interested?&nbsp; Sound like you?&nbsp; If so, we&rsquo;d love to hear from you.&nbsp; Please send us your resume, portfolio, and anything else that helps us understand who you are, what you can do and what you&rsquo;re looking for.&nbsp; Also, let us know the sites you think have the best design.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
You can reach us at <strong>jobs@pvpower.com</strong>.</p>
<p>
Thanks much.&nbsp; Looking forward to hearing from you.</p>
<p>
----</p>
<p>
More About PVPower:</p>
<p>
PVPower opened for business in early &lsquo;09.&nbsp; Since then we&rsquo;ve sold millions of dollars of solar components without help from any rock-stars or ninjas that we know of.&nbsp; Our office is a big and bright loft on the north side of Chicago along the Ravenswood corridor. We also have an office in the financial district of San Francisco. We are an <a href="http://exceleratelabs.com/">Excelerate Labs</a> company &ndash; class of 2010.&nbsp; A <a href="http://greenstart.com">Greentstart</a> company &ndash; class of 2012.&nbsp; We have a strong network of mentors and investors in Chicago, San Francisco, and across the country.&nbsp; And there&rsquo;s a place in our hearts for:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Creative problem solvers</li>
<li>
Working smart</li>
<li>
Learning new things and teaching others what we&rsquo;ve learned</li>
<li>
The Earth, its resources, and making sure it&rsquo;s all still around for our children and to enjoy</li>
</ul>
