			<description><![CDATA[<p>
Kiwi, a Chicago solar startup is seeking a jack-of-all-trades responsible for office management and bookkeeping.</p>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>The right candidate is&hellip;</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
A great person, looking for full to part-time, 2-5 days per week</li>
<li>
Expecting to earn $14-19 per hour based on their experience</li>
<li>
Looking for a positive, supportive and transparent working environment</li>
<li>
Detail oriented and organized</li>
<li>
Independent</li>
<li>
Dynamic and flexible</li>
<li>
A jack-of-all-trades</li>
<li>
Pro-active</li>
<li>
Reliable and trustworthy</li>
</ul>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>This position is responsible for&hellip;</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Bookkeeping in QuickBooks</li>
<li>
Accounts payable</li>
<li>
Making our office an even better place to work</li>
<li>
Helping with needs like data gathering, reporting and marketing support</li>
<li>
Coordinating travel, events and meetings</li>
<li>
Banking</li>
<li>
Coordinating with our accountant</li>
<li>
Keeping us organized and one-step-ahead</li>
</ul>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>Qualifications</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
2+ years of experience, ideally in an administrative, finance or accounting role</li>
<li>
Enthusiastic professional references</li>
<li>
Solid computer skills including MS Office, Windows, Google Calendar, Gmail, QB, etc.</li>
<li>
Bachelor&rsquo;s degree preferred but not required</li>
<li>
Comfortable with QuickBooks and bookkeeping</li>
<li>
Must be detail-oriented, reliable and proactive</li>
</ul>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>About Kiwi</strong><br />
We&rsquo;re a Chicago startup that is making it simple for homeowners to go solar across the country, check out our website at <a href="http://www.ownkiwi.com">http://www.ownkiwi.com</a>. We have four years of experience in the residential solar space (see <a href="http://www.pvpower.com">http://www.pvpower.com</a>) and have worked on over 200 solar projects across the country with homeowners and contractors. We&rsquo;re a group of passionate entrepreneurs with diverse backgrounds and an equal obsession with solar and technology. Our investors include some of Chicago&rsquo;s most-prominent entrepreneurs and we&rsquo;re growing fast. Our current loft space is located in the Ravenswood neighborhood near the Montrose brown line stop and we will be moving closer to downtown in the early spring.</p>
